headline: Goldman Sachs Asset Management Announces Changes to the Goldman Sachs ActiveBeta® World Low Vol Plus Equity ETF
summary: NEW YORK, January 30, 2026--Goldman Sachs Asset Management, L.P., the investment adviser for the Goldman Sachs ActiveBeta® World Low Vol Plus Equity ETF (the "Fund"), announced that the Fund’s Board of Trustees, at the recommendation of Goldman Sachs Asset Management, has approved changes to the Fund’s name, ticker, management fee and underlying index, together with related changes to the investment objective and principal investment strategy.

headline: Goldman Sachs Qatar Pact And Leadership Shift Spotlight Wealth Growth Focus
summary: Goldman Sachs Group (NYSE:GS) has entered a preliminary agreement with Qatar Investment Authority for up to US$25b in investments and co investment opportunities. The company is also adding seven leaders from its wealth and asset management division to the Goldman Sachs management committee. These moves combine a large international capital partnership with a reshaping of senior leadership in key growth focused businesses.
